cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper involves the use of deep learning models to analyze radiographs for the detection of hip fractures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the training of deep learning models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of patient and hospital process variables, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the need for further research to improve the cooperation between computers and clinicians, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
